MODE.description: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

ENDIAN.description: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian,  [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

TRIGGER.description: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

STATE.description: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

IV_MEM.description: The memory that stores initialization vector

H_MEM.description: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

DMA_ENABLE.description: 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

BLOCK_MODE.description: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

BLOCK_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

INC_SEL.description: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

AAD_BLOCK_NUM.description: Additional Authential Data block number register
Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

REMAINDER_BIT_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

CONTINUE.description: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

INT_CLEAR.description: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

DATE.description: This bits stores the version information of AES.

DMA_EXIT.description: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

IN_RST_CH0.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 0 Rx FSM and Rx FIFO pointer.

INDSCR_BURST_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

IN_DATA_BURST_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 receiving data when accessing internal SRAM.

MEM_TRANS_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit 1 to enable automatic transmitting data from memory to memory via DMA.

IN_CHECK_OWNER_CH0.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

INFIFO_EMPTY_CH0.description: L1 Rx FIFO empty signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_CNT_CH0.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L1 Rx FIFO for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_RDATA_CH0.description: This register stores the data popping from DMA FIFO.

INFIFO_POP_CH0.description: Set this bit to pop data from DMA FIFO.

INLINK_ADDR_CH0.description: This register stores the 20 least significant bits of the first inlink descriptor's address.

INLINK_AUTO_RET_CH0.description: Set this bit to return to current inlink descriptor's address, when there are some errors in current receiving data.

INLINK_STOP_CH0.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the inlink descriptors.

INLINK_START_CH0.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the inlink descriptors.

WB_MODE.description: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

CS0_DIS.description: SPI_CS0 pin enable, 1: disable SPI_CS0, 0: SPI_CS0 pin is active to select SPI device, such as flash, external RAM and so on.

CS1_DIS.description: SPI_CS1 pin enable, 1: disable SPI_CS1, 0: SPI_CS1 pin is active to select SPI device, such as flash, external RAM and so on.

CK_IDLE_EDGE.description: 1: spi clk line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle

CS_KEEP_ACTIVE.description: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set.

DATA.description: For SPI1, the value of crc32.

CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE.description: For SPI1,  cache  read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

FDIN_DUAL.description: For SPI1, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

FDOUT_DUAL.description: For SPI1, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

FADDR_DUAL.description: For SPI1, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

FDIN_QUAD.description: For SPI1, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

FDOUT_QUAD.description: For SPI1, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

FADDR_QUAD.description: For SPI1, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

WAITI_DUMMY.description: The dummy phase enable when wait flash idle (RDSR)

WAITI_CMD.description: The command to wait flash idle(RDSR).

WAITI_DUMMY_CYCLELEN.description: The dummy cycle length when wait flash idle(RDSR).

FLASH_PER.description: program erase resume bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

FLASH_PES.description: program erase suspend bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase resume command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase resume command is sent.

FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or *128) SPI_CLK cycles after program erase suspend command is sent. 0: SPI1 does not wait after program erase suspend command is sent.

PES_PER_EN.description: Set this bit to enable PES end triggers PER transfer option. If this bit is 0, application should send PER after PES is done.

FLASH_PES_EN.description: Set this bit to enable Auto-suspending function.

PESR_END_MSK.description: The mask value when check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. If the read status value is status_in[15:0](only status_in[7:0] is valid when only one byte of data is read out, status_in[15:0] is valid when two bytes of data are read out), SUS/SUS1/SUS2 = status_in[15:0]^ SPI_MEM_PESR_END_MSK[15:0].

RD_SUS_2B.description: 1: Read two bytes when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit. 0:  Read one byte when check flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit

PER_END_EN.description: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the resume status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

PES_END_EN.description: 1: Both WIP and SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits should be checked to insure the suspend status of flash. 0: Only need to check WIP is 0.

SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT.description: When SPI1 checks SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bits fail for SPI_MEM_SUS_TIMEOUT_CNT[6:0] times, it will be treated as check pass.

WAIT_PESR_COMMAND.description: Flash SUS/SUS1/SUS2 status bit read command. The command should be sent when SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit should be checked to insure the suspend or resume status of flash.

FLASH_SUS.description: The status of flash suspend, only used in SPI1.

WAIT_PESR_CMD_2B.description: 1: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[15:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit. 0: SPI1 sends out SPI_MEM_WAIT_PESR_COMMAND[7:0] to check SUS/SUS1/SUS2 bit.

FLASH_HPM_DLY_128.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent.

FLASH_RES_DLY_128.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent.

FLASH_DP_DLY_128.description: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent.

FLASH_PER_DLY_128.description: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent.

FLASH_PES_DLY_128.description: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 128) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent.

SPI0_LOCK_EN.description: 1: Enable SPI0 lock SPI0/1 arbiter option. 0: Disable it.

TIMING_CALI.description: The bit is used to enable timing auto-calibration for all reading operations.

EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN.description: add extra dummy spi clock cycle length for spi clock calibration.

PER_END_INT_ENA.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

PES_END_INT_ENA.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

WPE_END_INT_ENA.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt.

SLV_ST_END_INT_ENA.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

MST_ST_END_INT_ENA.description: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

PER_END_INT_CLR.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

PES_END_INT_CLR.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

MST_ST_END_INT_CLR.description: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

PER_END_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when Auto Resume command (0x7A) is sent and flash is resumed. 0: Others.

PES_END_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.1: Triggered when Auto Suspend command (0x75) is sent and flash is suspended. 0: Others.

WPE_END_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_WPE_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is sent and flash is already idle. 0: Others.

SLV_ST_END_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_slv_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. It means that SPI_CS raises high. 0: Others

MST_ST_END_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi1_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

PES_END_INT_ST.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

SLV_ST_END_INT_ST.description: The status bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

CLK_EN.description: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

CONF_BITLEN.description: Define the APB cycles of  SPI_CONF state. Can be configured in CONF state.

UPDATE.description: Set this bit to synchronize SPI registers from APB clock domain into SPI module clock domain, which is only used in SPI master mode.

USR.description: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable. Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

USR_ADDR_VALUE.description: Address to slave. Can be configured in CONF state.

DUMMY_OUT.description: In the dummy phase the signal level of spi is output by the spi controller. Can be configured in CONF state.

FADDR_DUAL.description: Apply 2 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

FADDR_QUAD.description: Apply 4 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

FCMD_DUAL.description: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

FCMD_QUAD.description: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

FREAD_DUAL.description: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

FREAD_QUAD.description: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

Q_POL.description: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

D_POL.description: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

HOLD_POL.description: SPI_HOLD output value when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

WP_POL.description: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.  Can be configured in CONF state.

RD_BIT_ORDER.description: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

WR_BIT_ORDER.description: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

CLKCNT_L.description: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

CLKCNT_H.description: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

CLKCNT_N.description: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

CLKDIV_PRE.description: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.  Can be configured in CONF state.

CLK_EQU_SYSCLK.description: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

DOUTDIN.description: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

QPI_MODE.description: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

TSCK_I_EDGE.description: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

CS_HOLD.description: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS_SETUP.description: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

RSCK_I_EDGE.description: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

CK_OUT_EDGE.description: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

FWRITE_DUAL.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

FWRITE_QUAD.description: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_CONF_NXT.description: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

SIO.description: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_MISO_HIGHPART.description: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_MOSI_HIGHPART.description: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_DUMMY_IDLE.description: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_MOSI.description: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_MISO.description: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_DUMMY.description: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_ADDR.description: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_COMMAND.description: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN.description: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

MST_WFULL_ERR_END_EN.description: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

CS_SETUP_TIME.description: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_setup bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS_HOLD_TIME.description: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_hold bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_ADDR_BITLEN.description: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

USR_COMMAND_VALUE.description: The value of  command. Can be configured in CONF state.

MST_REMPTY_ERR_END_EN.description: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

USR_COMMAND_BITLEN.description: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

MS_DLEN.description: SPI data bit length control register

MS_DATA_BITLEN.description: The value of these bits is the configured SPI transmission data bit length in master mode DMA controlled transfer or CPU controlled transfer. The value is also the configured bit length in slave mode DMA RX controlled transfer. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

CS0_DIS.description: SPI CS0 pin enable, 1: disable CS0, 0: spi_cs0 signal is from/to CS0 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS1_DIS.description: SPI CS1 pin enable, 1: disable CS1, 0: spi_cs1 signal is from/to CS1 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS2_DIS.description: SPI CS2 pin enable, 1: disable CS2, 0: spi_cs2 signal is from/to CS2 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS3_DIS.description: SPI CS3 pin enable, 1: disable CS3, 0: spi_cs3 signal is from/to CS3 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS4_DIS.description: SPI CS4 pin enable, 1: disable CS4, 0: spi_cs4 signal is from/to CS4 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS5_DIS.description: SPI CS5 pin enable, 1: disable CS5, 0: spi_cs5 signal is from/to CS5 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

CK_DIS.description: 1: spi clk out disable,  0: spi clk out enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

MASTER_CS_POL.description: In the master mode the bits are the polarity of spi cs line, the value is equivalent to spi_cs ^ spi_master_cs_pol. Can be configured in CONF state.

SLAVE_CS_POL.description: spi slave input cs polarity select. 1: inv  0: not change. Can be configured in CONF state.

CK_IDLE_EDGE.description: 1: spi clk line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle. Can be configured in CONF state.

CS_KEEP_ACTIVE.description: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set. Can be configured in CONF state.

QUAD_DIN_PIN_SWAP.description: 1:  spi quad input swap enable  0:  spi quad input swap disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN0_MODE.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN1_MODE.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN2_MODE.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN3_MODE.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: input without delayed, 1: input with the posedge of clk_apb,2 input with the negedge of clk_apb, 3: input with the spi_clk. Can be configured in CONF state.

TIMING_HCLK_ACTIVE.description: 1:enable hclk in SPI input timing module.  0: disable it. Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN0_NUM.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,...  Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN1_NUM.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,...  Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN2_NUM.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,...  Can be configured in CONF state.

DIN3_NUM.description: the input signals are delayed by SPI module clock cycles, 0: delayed by 1 cycle, 1: delayed by 2 cycles,...  Can be configured in CONF state.

DOUT0_MODE.description: The output signal 0 is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

DOUT1_MODE.description: The output signal 1 is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

DOUT2_MODE.description: The output signal 2 is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

DOUT3_MODE.description: The output signal 3 is delayed by the SPI module clock, 0: output without delayed, 1: output delay for a SPI module clock cycle at its negative edge. Can be configured in CONF state.

SLV_RX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN.description: 1: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 5. 0: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

LINESIZE.description: This bit stores the line size parameter. 0: 16Byte, 1: 32Byte.

DESTINATION.description: This bit stores the destination. 0: flash(default). 1: reserved.

PHYSICAL_ADDRESS.description: Those bits stores the physical address. If linesize is 16-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 16 bytes. If linesize is 32-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 32 bytes.

TRIGGER.description: Set this bit to start manual encryption calculation

RELEASE.description: Set this bit to release the manual encrypted result, after that the result will be visible to spi

DESTROY.description: Set this bit to destroy XTS-AES result.

STATE.description: Those bits shows XTS-AES status. 0=IDLE, 1=WORK, 2=RELEASE, 3=USE. IDLE means that XTS-AES is idle. WORK means that XTS-AES is busy with calculation. RELEASE means the encrypted result is generated but not visible to mspi. USE means that the encrypted result is visible to mspi.

DATE.description: Those bits stores the version information of XTS-AES.

RESET_MODE.description: This bit is used to configure the operating mode of the TWAI Controller. 1: Reset mode; 0: Operating mode.

LISTEN_ONLY_MODE.description: 1: Listen only mode. In this mode the nodes will only receive messages from the bus, without generating the acknowledge signal nor updating the RX error counter.

SELF_TEST_MODE.description: 1: Self test mode. In this mode the TX nodes can perform a successful transmission without receiving the acknowledge signal. This mode is often used to test a single node with the self reception request command.

RX_FILTER_MODE.description: This bit is used to configure the filter mode. 0: Dual filter mode; 1: Single filter mode.

TX_REQ.description: Set the bit to 1 to allow the driving nodes start transmission.

ABORT_TX.description: Set the bit to 1 to cancel a pending transmission request.

RELEASE_BUF.description: Set the bit to 1 to release the RX buffer.

CLR_OVERRUN.description: Set the bit to 1 to clear the data overrun status bit.

SELF_RX_REQ.description: Self reception request command. Set the bit to 1 to allow a message be transmitted and received simultaneously.

RX_BUF_ST.description: 1: The data in the RX buffer is not empty, with at least one received data packet.

OVERRUN_ST.description: 1: The RX FIFO is full and data overrun has occurred.

TX_BUF_ST.description: 1: The TX buffer is empty, the CPU may write a message into it.

TX_COMPLETE.description: 1: The TWAI controller has successfully received a packet from the bus.

RX_ST.description: 1: The TWAI Controller is receiving a message from the bus.

TX_ST.description: 1: The TWAI Controller is transmitting a message to the bus.

ERR_ST.description: 1: At least one of the RX/TX error counter has reached or exceeded the value set in register TWAI_ERR_WARNING_LIMIT_REG.

BUS_OFF_ST.description: 1: In bus-off status, the TWAI Controller is no longer involved in bus activities.

MISS_ST.description: This bit reflects whether the data packet in the RX FIFO is complete. 1: The current packet is missing; 0: The current packet is complete

RX_INT_ST.description: Receive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates there are messages to be handled in the RX FIFO.

TX_INT_ST.description: Transmit interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the message transmitting mis- sion is finished and a new transmission is able to execute.

ERR_WARN_INT_ST.description: Error warning interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the error status signal and the bus-off status signal of Status register have changed (e.g., switched from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0).

OVERRUN_INT_ST.description: Data overrun interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates a data overrun interrupt is generated in the RX FIFO.

ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ST.description: Error passive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the TWAI Controller is switched between error active status and error passive status due to the change of error counters.

ARB_LOST_INT_ST.description: Arbitration lost interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an arbitration lost interrupt is generated.

BUS_ERR_INT_ST.description: Error interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an error is detected on the bus.

RXD_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

CTS_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

DSR_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

TXD_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

RTS_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

DTR_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

CLK_EN.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

ERR_WR_MASK.description: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

AUTOBAUD_EN.description: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

MEM_CLK_EN.description: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD.description: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD.description: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

DIS_RX_DAT_OVF.description: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS.description: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

RX_FLOW_EN.description: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

RX_TOUT_EN.description: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

LOWPULSE.description: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

MIN_CNT.description: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

HIGHPULSE.description: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

MIN_CNT.description: This register stores  the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

RXD_EDGE_CNT.description: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

SW_FLOW_CON_EN.description: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

XONOFF_DEL.description: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

FORCE_XON.description: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

FORCE_XOFF.description: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

SEND_XON.description: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

SEND_XOFF.description: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

ACTIVE_THRESHOLD.description: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

XOFF_THRESHOLD.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xoff char.

XOFF_CHAR.description: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

XON_THRESHOLD.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xon char.

XON_CHAR.description: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

TX_BRK_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

RX_IDLE_THRHD.description: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

TX_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

RS485_EN.description: Set this bit to choose the rs485 mode.

DL0_EN.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

DL1_EN.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

RS485TX_RX_EN.description: Set this bit to enable receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in rs485 mode.

RS485RXBY_TX_EN.description: 1'h1: enable rs485 transmitter to send data when rs485 receiver line is busy.

RS485_RX_DLY_NUM.description: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

RS485_TX_DLY_NUM.description: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

PRE_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

POST_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

RX_GAP_TOUT.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

AT_CMD_CHAR.description: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

CHAR_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

RX_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for receive-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

TX_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for transmit-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

RX_FLOW_THRHD.description: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

RX_TOUT_THRHD.description: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

MEM_FORCE_PD.description: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

MEM_FORCE_PU.description: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

MEM_TX_STATUS.description: Tx-FIFO write and read offset address.

APB_TX_WADDR.description: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when software writes Tx-FIFO via APB.

TX_RADDR.description: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when Tx-FSM reads data via Tx-FIFO_Ctrl.

MEM_RX_STATUS.description: Rx-FIFO write and read offset address.

APB_RX_RADDR.description: This register stores the offset address in RX-FIFO when software reads data from Rx-FIFO via APB. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

RX_WADDR.description: This register stores the offset address in Rx-FIFO when Rx-FIFO_Ctrl writes Rx-FIFO. UART0 is 10'h100. UART1 is 10'h180.

ST_URX_OUT.description: This is the status register of receiver.

ST_UTX_OUT.description: This is the status register of transmitter.

POSEDGE_MIN_CNT.description: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT.description: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

SCLK_DIV_B.description: The  denominator of the frequency divider factor.

SCLK_DIV_A.description: The numerator of the frequency divider factor.

SCLK_DIV_NUM.description: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

SCLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable UART Tx/Rx clock.

RST_CORE.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx/Rx.

TX_SCLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

RX_SCLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

TX_RST_CORE.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx.

RX_RST_CORE.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Rx.

ID.description: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

HIGH_SPEED.description: This bit used to select synchronize mode. 1: Registers are auto synchronized into UART Core clock and UART core should be keep the same with APB clock. 0: After configure registers, software needs to write 1 to UART_REG_UPDATE to synchronize registers.

REG_UPDATE.description: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

RDWR_BYTE.description: Write and read byte data to/from UART Tx/Rx FIFO through this field. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT is set, then user can write data (up to 64 bytes) into UART Tx FIFO. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is set, user can check USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP0_RD_ADDR to know how many data is received, then read data from UART Rx FIFO.

WR_DONE.description: Set this bit to indicate writing byte data to UART Tx FIFO is done.

SERIAL_IN_EP_DATA_FREE.description: 1'b1: Indicate UART Tx FIFO is not full and can write data into in. After writing USB_DEVICE_WR_DONE, this bit would be 0 until data in UART Tx FIFO is read by USB Host.

SERIAL_OUT_EP_DATA_AVAIL.description: 1'b1: Indicate there is data in UART Rx FIFO.

JTAG_IN_FLUSH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when flush cmd is received for IN endpoint 2 of JTAG.

SOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when SOF frame is received.

SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port OUT Endpoint received one packet.

SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port IN Endpoint is empty.

PID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when pid error is detected.

CRC5_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC5 error is detected.

CRC16_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC16 error is detected.

STUFF_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when stuff error is detected.

IN_TOKEN_REC_IN_EP1_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when IN token for IN endpoint 1 is received.

USB_BUS_RESET_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when usb bus reset is detected.

OUT_EP1_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when OUT endpoint 1 received packet with zero palyload.

OUT_EP2_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when OUT endpoint 2 received packet with zero palyload.
